 Governor Abdullahi Sule of Nasarawa State has approved the appointment of Mr Muhammed Ubandoma-Aliyu as the Secretary to the State Government (SSG). This is contained in a statement signed by Yakubu Lamai, Director-General, Strategic Communication and Press Affairs to the governor and made available to newsmen on Wednesday in Lafia. According to the statement, the appointment of Ubandoma-Aliyu takes effect immediately. The statement added that the new SSG, before this appointment, was a principal partner at M.U Aliyu Chambers Lafia. He isÂ also a former Chairman of Lafia Local Government Area (LGA), from 1999 to 2002. Recall that the former SSG, Alhaji Aliyu Ahmed-Tijani, was sacked by the governor. (NAN)